<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-09-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-09-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="125" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d125">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Diplomatic Agent <persName type="to">Jackson</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <hi rend="italic"><date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-09-24">September 24,
                                        1906</date></hi>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Informs him that the President signed, September 15, a proclamation of a
                            commercial arrangement with Bulgaria, to take effect September 30.
                            States that a formal exchange of notes may be made reciting date if
                            practicable. Reply to his telegram of September 18.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>